<div class='about-page'><h1>Minerva ballet</h1>
<h2>Information for Dancers</h2>

<h3>1. Personnel</h3> 
<p>1.1 The company director and founder is Patrick Hood<br>
1.2 Patrick Hood is Artistic Director<br>
1.3 Sheila Styles is ballet mistress and coach<br>
1.4 Others will be appointed for specialist coaching at the discretion of the Artistic Director</p>

<h3>2. Ethos of the company</h3>
<p>2.1 Minerva Ballet is an adult ballet company seeking to present professional performances<br>
2.2 A professional attitude is expected by all involved.  This includes good time keeping, good attendance, and maintenance of good technique through attending appropriate, approved classes outside rehearsal time.  Women must attend at least one pointe class per week</p>

<h3>3. Repertoire and casting</h3>
<p>3.1 Casting and repertoire decisions are the sole responsibility of the Artistic Director. The Programme will be determined for the next performance and casting will be based on ability and suitability.  If dancers wish to discuss dancing a particular role, they may do so, but inclusion in any programme is not guaranteed.   This is to ensure that artistic integrity and standards are maintained.<br>
3.2 Any proposals for repertoire will be approved by the Artistic Director to ensure suitability and feasibility.<br>
3.3 Casting is dependent on good attendance and performance.  If the Artistic Director feels that a dancer is underperforming, they will be recast.</p> 

<h3>4. Principal Roles</h3>
<p>4.1 Casting in a principal role is at the discretion of the Artistic Director.  No petitions for roles will be accepted. <br>
4.2 Principals will be required to undertake private coaching sessions with the Artistic director or a nominated coach.<br>
4.3 Regular attendance at approved classes will be required for all those cast in a principal role.</p>

<h3>5. Conduct during rehearsals</h3>
<p>5.1 Courtesy should be shown to all with noise levels kept to a minimum.<br>
5.2 Use of mobile phones should be kept to an absolute minimum.<br>
5.3 Videos should be used for critique, not for learning repertoire, and will be permitted on this basis.<br>
5.4 All dancers should get into the habit of bringing a notebook to rehearsals and recording the repertoire which has been covered.<br>
5.5 Timekeeping is of the utmost importance.</p>

